---
import PublicLayout from '../layouts/PublicLayout.astro';
---

<PublicLayout
  title="About"
  description="Meet James Farley, agile consultant and founder of smagile. A remote-first consultancy focused on practical support for product teams."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-grey-900 dark:text-white">About smagile</h1>

    <div class="mt-8 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        smagile is a remote-first agile consultancy offering specialist support to product teams,
        along with training and coaching for professionals working in agile environments.
      </p>

      <h2>James Farley</h2>
      <p>
        James refers to himself as an "agile consultant", as although Scrum Mastery has been an
        important part of his journey, he enjoys serving teams and organisations in various roles
        and accountabilities.
      </p>
      <p>
        "Mastery" is a relentless pursuit that drives James and his service to teams. With over
        a decade of experience supporting product teams of varying degrees of agile maturity,
        from complete novice to seasoned practitioner, he brings practical, hands-on expertise
        to every engagement.
      </p>
      <p>
        James is a licensed ProKanban.org trainer, accredited to teach the application of
        Professional Kanban. He develops bespoke agile training that has been refined over
        years of real-world delivery.
      </p>

      <h2>Our approach</h2>
      <p>
        We believe in meeting teams where they are. There is no single framework or methodology
        that fits every context. Instead, we listen, observe, and work alongside your people to
        find what works for them.
      </p>
      <p>
        We value neurodiversity, celebrate failure as a route to learning, and believe that
        integrity and psychological safety are the foundations of high-performing teams.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</PublicLayout>
